"v. 反刍；深思 【英】 v. 反刍; 深思(to turn sth. over in the mind; meditate) 【例】 The owner ruminated about giving the workers a raise. 无 【记】音：乳糜，一种类似酸奶的乳制品，牛把乳糜反刍；音：肉糜 + in + ate 吃，将酸奶，肉吃进去反复嚼成肉糜，反复咀嚼，琢磨，引申为沉思；音：入迷→沉思 ruminate (v.)  1530s, ""to turn over in the mind,"" also ""to chew cud"" (1540s), from Latin ruminatus, past participle of ruminare ""to chew the cud; turn over in the mind,"" from rumen (genitive ruminis) ""gullet,"" of uncertain origin. Related: Ruminated; ruminating."
